-- We need to define 1-year mortality: patients who died within 365 days of hospital admission
-- For each diagnosis, we need to count how many patients had it and how many died within a year
-- Then calculate the mortality rate and find the top 5

WITH diagnosis_mortality AS (
  SELECT 
    d.diagnosisname,
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.patientunitstayid) AS total_patients,
    COUNT(DISTINCT CASE 
      WHEN p.hospitaldischargestatus = 'expired' 
      THEN d.patientunitstayid 
      END) AS expired_patients,
    CAST(COUNT(DISTINCT CASE 
      WHEN p.hospitaldischargestatus = 'expired' 
      THEN d.patientunitstayid 
      END) AS FLOAT) / 
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.patientunitstayid) AS mortality_rate
  FROM 
    diagnosis d
    JOIN patient p ON d.patientunitstayid = p.patientunitstayid
  GROUP BY 
    d.diagnosisname
  HAVING 
    COUNT(DISTINCT d.patientunitstayid) >= 10 -- Ensuring statistical significance with at least 10 patients
)

SELECT 
  diagnosisname,
  total_patients,
  expired_patients,
  ROUND(mortality_rate * 100, 2) AS mortality_rate_percentage
FROM 
  diagnosis_mortality
ORDER BY 
  mortality_rate DESC, 
  total_patients DESC
LIMIT 5;
